Cell.Text: I have no idea what you're talking about. You know, that man is a scoundrel and a liar.

Node.Caption: _arcQuest001TelishaRingBranchStart: Calder told me you cheated him out of his mother's ring.

Cell.Text: So naturally, we put a stop to it. He behaved himself for a while, but we could tell he was still pushing his luck every now and then. | I grew tired of his antics. So, one night, I challenged him to a game of coin toss. Anyway, after losing all of his gold to me, I made him a deal. | I told him that if he won, I would give him all of his gold back. But if I won, he would be banned from entering The Four Shields forever. | Well...you can see for yourself how things turned out. I do feel kind of bad for him though.
You seem to be avoiding the subject...

If you want to talk about a fictional ring, I suggest you go and consult Calder, or go and read a book about one, | because it's the first time I've heard of it. Perhaps he's trying to turn you against me? It wouldn't be surprising. | He's certainly not above such blatant manipulation of the folks in these parts.

[S] I suppose I should be happy about that then. I can appreciate your skepticism though. | If I'm being completely honest, I do have some idea as to why he would manufacture a story about a ring... | But I cannot talk about it, or else I would be breaking a very special promise I made to someone. I hope you can understand.
I'm going to force the truth out of you. (Brawl)
[S] G|If you don't believe me, there's not much I can do about it then. Feel free to do what you will, I don't like your chances though. | I can handle myself pretty well!
Have you ever considered why no one in town wants him here?
Have you ever considered why no one wants him in Dragon Bridge?
Calder frequented this tavern. He would slink in and out of here as he pleased, soliciting drinks to our customers.
Calder frequented The Four Shields. He would slink in and out of there as he pleased, soliciting drinks to our customers.

Node.Caption: _arcQuest001TelishaRingBranchThinkYes: No, I haven't. Can you tell me why?
